321
00:30:52,960 --> 00:30:58,720
But this one's from the one about France, where 
Tocqueville observes, "The most dangerous moment  

322
00:30:58,720 --> 00:31:05,120
for a bad government is when it begins to reform."
Russians of all political persuasions  

323
00:31:05,120 --> 00:31:09,680
agree on at least one thing.
That is that Gorbachev's role in  

324
00:31:09,680 --> 00:31:14,880
how the Cold War turned out was pivotal, 
that he played a very essential part. 

325
00:31:14,880 --> 00:31:19,280
Gorbachev made his decision based 
on certain false assumptions. 

326
00:31:19,280 --> 00:31:22,480
One of them was the irreversible 
direction of history. 

327
00:31:22,480 --> 00:31:29,120
Gorbachev thought of history going always forward 
towards communism, never backwards to capitalism. 

328
00:31:29,120 --> 00:31:33,040
Of course, Eastern Europe took a U-turn, 
went straight back to capitalism. 

329
00:31:33,040 --> 00:31:40,000
Here is Leonid Shebarshin, who is a senior 
person in the KGB, their intelligence office. 

330
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:43,200
He said, "The thought never occurred 
to the government that it's possible  

331
00:31:43,200 --> 00:31:48,560
to withdraw from socialism."
If you think about both communist  

332
00:31:48,560 --> 00:31:54,640
