335
00:32:07,280 --> 00:32:14,240
It was like a donut empire.
So when the empire went to Eastern Europe,  

336
00:32:14,880 --> 00:32:20,640
Russians could no longer siphon off the wealth 
of these enserfed populations in Eastern Europe,  

337
00:32:20,640 --> 00:32:26,000
which explains why they wanted to leave.
It also suggests why Putin wants them back. 

338
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:30,240
Another false assumption has to do 
with the sentiments of the neighbors. 

339
00:32:30,240 --> 00:32:34,160
Gorbachev was convinced he was going to 
get credit for liberating Eastern Europe,  

340
00:32:34,160 --> 00:32:38,480
rather than blame as a Russian for 
having enserfed them in the first place. 

341
00:32:38,480 --> 00:32:44,160
For Gorbachev, the clock began on his watch.
For other people, no, Stalin's when it began,  

342
00:32:44,160 --> 00:32:48,640
when he started shooting a lot of people.
Here you have Anatoly Chernyaev,  

343
00:32:48,640 --> 00:32:54,960
foreign policy adviser to Gorbachev, saying 
that Gorbachev thought that bringing freedom  

344
00:32:54,960 --> 00:33:00,080
to our Eastern European satellites would 
